name: Jamaica
summary: Hurricane Beryl, now a Category 4 storm, has wreaked havoc as it made its way through the Caribbean. Jamaica, in particular, has been experiencing the brunt of the storm's powerful winds and torrential rains, leading to significant damage and power outages. The storm has also caused widespread destruction in Grenada, with the leader describing the damage as "unimaginable." As Hurricane Beryl approaches Jamaica, residents are bracing for life-threatening winds and storm surges. The outer bands of the storm have already begun battering the island, and a vacationing family from New Jersey has been left stranded due to the approaching hurricane. The death toll from the storm has risen to at least seven, and prime minister of Jamaica has declared the island a "disaster area."

name: Lloyd Doggett
summary: Rep. Lloyd Doggett, a Democrat from Texas, has become the first sitting Democratic member of Congress to call on President Biden to withdraw from the 2024 presidential race. Doggett's call reflects growing concerns within the Democratic Party about Biden's age and his ability to withstand a rigorous campaign. Doggett's announcement has been met with mixed reactions, with some fellow Democrats expressing support while others have defended Biden's record and his right to seek re-election. The Republican Party has seized on Doggett's comments as evidence of Democratic disarray and has stepped up pressure on Biden to end his campaign.

name: Rudy Giuliani
summary: Rudy Giuliani, a former New York City mayor and personal lawyer to Donald Trump, has been disbarred in New York for making false and misleading statements about the 2020 presidential election. The New York State Appellate Division, First Department found that Giuliani repeatedly made baseless claims of widespread voter fraud, undermining the integrity of the election and the rule of law. The court cited numerous instances where Giuliani made false and misleading statements, including allegations that voting machines were rigged and that millions of illegal votes were cast. The court's ruling is a significant blow to Giuliani's legal career and reputation, and it comes as he faces criminal indictments related to his efforts to overturn the 2020 election results.
